<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="166" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1436,291,786]" pageId="15" pageNumber="166">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,335,687,714]" pageId="15" pageNumber="166">Comments.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Esposito" authorityYear="1994" box="[343,613,688,714]" class="Insecta" family="Agromyzidae" genus="Calycomyza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="166" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ipomoensis">
<emphasis box="[343,613,688,714]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="166">Calycomyza ipomoensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Spencer" authorityName="Spencer" box="[760,1011,688,715]" class="Insecta" family="Agromyzidae" genus="Calycomyza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="166" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="stegmaieri">
<emphasis box="[760,912,689,715]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="166">C. stegmaieri</emphasis>
Spencer
</taxonomicName>
, from which it is differentiated by the shape of the distiphallus. So far, this species has only been associated with 
<taxonomicName box="[985,1198,724,750]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Ipomoea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="15" pageNumber="166" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="asarifolia">
<emphasis box="[985,1198,724,750]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="166">Ipomoea asarifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, forming blotches on the surface of the leaf with frass deposited in continuous lines.
</paragraph>
